    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="824"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d824">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 652.119/1806</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The War Trade Board Representative in Cuba</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MHH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Chief of the Division of Latin American
                        Affairs</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SJH2" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stabler</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 14, 1918</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received August 22.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_HHC1"
                            >Herbert</persName>
                    </hi>: Referring to my letter of August 10, 1918, I now have to inform you that
                    I had a conversation with the Spanish Minister two days ago in reference to
                    bunkering the Spanish steamers at Porto Rico or some other American port, and he
                    advised me that he would telegraph his recommendations to the Spanish
                    Government, and hoped to receive a favorable reply within a few days.</p>
                <p>As soon as I hear from him upon the subject I will at once let you know.</p>
                <p>Yours very sincerely,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MHH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">H. H. Morgan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
